# Everden QA Checklist

Before ending a session or starting the next feature (T3, T5, T9, etc.):

1. Read `docs/PROGRESS.md` — update % and append CHECKIN.
2. Run `npm test && npm run typecheck && npm run build`.
3. **Visual/play gate** (presentation, scenes, input — see `everden-visual-gate.mdc`):
   - Run **everden-visual-scout** in browser (gates G1–G5)
   - Log to `docs/playtests/AGENT_RUNS.md` — agent runs ≠ human T8
   - **FAIL** → do not bump Experience %; fix blockers first
   - Lilymarket / district composition → **Nick eye test** before PASS
4. For gameplay logic-only changes, verify in browser (`npm run dev`):
   - Main quest: 4 examines → council vote → gold/flags
   - Ferry quest: Grizz toll line → Jenna (quest-gated) → Grizz report line (quest-gated)
   - Combat: enemy turns fire, abilities work, flee ends turn on fail
   - Save/load: quest stage + species + scene persist
5. Fix **known gaps** listed in latest CHECKIN or `AGENT_RUNS.md` before adding new scope.
6. Add a unit test for each bug fixed (regression guard).

## Two tracks

| Track | Tool | Gates Experience %? |
|-------|------|---------------------|
| Mechanical | `npm test` | No (regression only) |
| Visual/play | Scout + persona agents + Nick | Yes, after PASS |

See `docs/systems/VISUAL_QA_AGENTS.md` and `.cursor/skills/everden-playtest/SKILL.md`.

## Do not ship without

- Enemy AI on enemy turns
- Save not clobbering active quests
- Conditions that are logged affecting mechanics
- Dialogue conditions for quest-specific lines

## Honesty

Vertical slice ~50% ≠ shippable. See `everden-progress.mdc`.
